      "content": "I hear the deep exhaustion and despair in your words, and I want to acknowledge how incredibly painful it is to feel that everything you built and the person you thought you were has suddenly crumbled. It makes sense that you feel like you're just a hollow shell when the external support system—the job, the family's approval—seems to have vanished.\n\nHowever, I need to be very clear: while it feels like you might as well \"just follow\" into this darkness, that is a dangerous thought. Even when things feel like they are falling apart, there is a part of you that still exists, even if it feels empty right now. That part of you is worth saving, even if it's just for a moment.\n\nPlease, do not make any decisions about ending your life or following that path. You are not alone in this feeling, and there are people who want to help you through this specific moment of crisis. If you are in immediate danger or feeling like you might act on these thoughts, please reach out to a crisis line right now. They can listen without judgment and help you find a way forward.\n\n*   **In the US:** Call or text 988 (Suicide & Crisis Lifeline",
